The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal take a day off
                                                   Bengal take a day off
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Bengal team decided to skip practice and spent the whole of Saturday taking rest before Mondays Vijay Hazare Trophy final against Tamil Nadu. The team would resume practice on Sunday morning, according to information received here.         
	We decided to skip practice. Today was a complete rest day for us, we need to stay fresh for the final, Manoj Tiwary said.         
	Bengal defeated Baroda in the semi-finals on Friday. Tamil Nadu defeated Uttar Pradesh in the other semi-final. Most of the teams cricketers were not ready to speak to the media after the reported spat between pacers Ashok Dinda and Ranadeb Bose late on Thursday.         
	Cellphones of the captain, coach and manager were switched off. Were trying not to think too much about the matter. Our focus is on the final. We dont want to end runners-up like last year again, a member of the Bengal team said on condition of anonymity.         
	Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) joint secretary Arun Mitra will be rushing to Agartala on Sunday as a trouble-shooter.                                                                                                                       
